node.text: It’s no secret that one of my pals got me hooked on #Crocs during our last collective year of work-from-home. And I got hooked on gardening! Running a small hobby farm from home has me doubling down on making sure I’m taking care of my own environment, and the planet at large. So to be one of the first friends to receive the Crocs of the future!? I’m so impressed with these bio-based comfies! #ComfortWithoutCarbon is here. And it’s a hit at our house. Thanks to my pals @crocs for the wonderful surprise — and for sending such a happy gift that came in FULLY compostable and recycled packaging. Putting all of this confetti in our compost bin was fun! 🎉 More of this, please. #ad 🌱 #hobbyfarm #compost #compostable #netzero #goals

node.text: Yes please! @tinatchen joins me today to discuss the #CTC and give you all of the details you’ll need to sign up — did you know that visiting www.ChildTaxCredit.gov and filling out your info ALSO qualifies you to receive any stimulus checks you might have missed due to your filing status!? — or to help your loved ones do so. This money is a game changer for ALL families. In every state. Because the quality of children’s lives isn’t partisan. Let’s go, friends!

node.text: Today I’m joined by two of my ocean heroes, Dr. Ayana Elizabeth Johnson and Philippe Cousteau, to discuss why our current climate crisis must be taken seriously, but also fills us with optimism and inspiration. Hint: young people have a lot to do with solutions! Change and community uplift and economic empowerment and cultural wealth are all possible when we prioritize climate! So let’s goooo 🤍💙

node.text: [CONT’D 2] Jared Yates Sexton rightly pointed out that “The entire reason we have rules to expel members of Congress is to expel members of Congress who have openly endorsed the murder of their colleagues, traffic in racist, virulent conspiracy theories, and have worked to overthrow the government.” That day? Over 140 officers injured. Two officers are dead from the attack; two from suicide. Officers without helmets sustained brain injuries. One officer has two cracked ribs and two smashed spinal discs. One officer is going to lose his eye; one was stabbed with a metal fence stake. And people like Lauren Boebert gave tours?! Greene says these are patriots?? Ted Cruz spoke at the rallies screaming “don’t go quietly!!” Madison Cawthorn told supporters “you can threaten” your reps over the election. Don’t even get me started on Josh Hawley. And these are the same people, who despite having facts about @ayannapressley’s panic buttons having been ripped out of her Congressional office ahead of the attack, despite the published evidence that Christopher Miller, Trump's then-acting defense secretary, on Jan 4 issued a memorandum stating that authorities at the Capitol were not allowed to use weapons, wear helmets or body armor, interact physically with protestors, employ riot control agents, or even make arrests, essentially guaranteeing that the insurrection would succeed, want to move on!? You’re damn right I agree with Rep @jackiespeier that inciting insurrection and being a terrorist sympathizer in the halls of Congress or the Senate means you should be labeled as such. But what Breitbart did, falsely claiming I am “advocating for labeling [ALL] Republicans as terrorists,” misrepresenting my agreement with Congressional leaders about the standard to which their colleagues are held and obfuscating my point to claim I’m apparently passing judgment on anyone who’s ever voted as a registered conservative? It’s egregious and irresponsible. It lacks context or the critical thinking skills required to make nuanced points. But the thing is?? They know that. “News” editors do pay attention, and do know what the argument is. [CONT]

node.text:
My fellow Californians! Vote NO on the #recall! You have until 8pm tonight to get your ballots in! You can also vote in person at your polling place, and they offer same day registration. Swipe for info! 

Today we have a chance to stand up against partisan nonsense that’s attempting to derail our democratic process. We have a gubernatorial election coming next year, but the GOP doesn’t care about that and has instead wasted almost $70 MILLION in our state taxpayer money and all of our time with this recall. What’s at stake? Climate protections (in a wildfire state no less!), science, pandemic response, women’s health, and so much more. Let’s not let anti-science sensationalists who believe that former slave owners (yes, ENSLAVERS) are owed reparations (Larry Elder) or that private jet owners should pay LESS taxes (Caitlyn Jenner) take over the world’s fifth largest economy and kneecap the progress we’re finally making after a pandemic crisis. Or threaten free lunches for all kids in every California school. Because Newsom did that while hunger spiked during COVID. That’s where money should be going (not this recall bs). He’s prioritizing kids while the rest of them are, well, you read what they want to invest in. You don’t have to think he’s perfect, that’s okay. But if not? Let’s have a real election next year and let people run on plans, not controversial soundbites and clickbait.

Our residents deserves leadership that cares about folks across our incredible state. From farm towns to big cities, from creatives to industrial job teams to gig workers. We need bold plans that can be nation-leading ideas. And we should get to hear those plans and scrutinize them and debate them in a real election next year. Let’s stand up for democracy and do things right. Vote no! See y’all at the polls ♥️🗳✌🏼

node.text: My sweet Papa turned 74 yesterday. He’s such a good man. And a great dad. Watching the ducks with him over a cup of coffee in the morning is a gift. The fact that he brings a bag of tools with him — stashed in the trunk of his car — just in case we ever need help fixing something is the most precious little act of love. Celebrating him brings me tremendous joy. I love watching him and Grant nerd out about wine. And watching him and my mom hold hands when they walk down the street even still, though they’ve been married over 40 years. And I also really love my Dad getting fired about the dumpster fire that is #SB8, grumbling that “all these selfish f*ckers (the men making such laws) should get mandatory vasectomies to prove their commitment to stopping pregnancies if they want to legislate other people’s bodies so badly.” Dad. You’re a fiery feminist, and a truly great ally, and we love to see it. Happy birthday to my original ride or die. I love you. 💞🔥🦆

node.text:
Approved! Swipe for ALL the info! Highlight reel:

✅ vaccines are safe
✅ vaccines are effective
✅ the vaccines are not experimental 
✅ and this vaccine is now fully APPROVED

No, this vaccine wasn’t “rushed,” both the vaxx and the lipid nanoparticles for its delivery took several decades. And no, it’s not “experimental.” mRNA testing has been extensive in treatments for 7 other infectious diseases, cancers, AND genetic disorders. It is not new, experimental, or “gene therapy.” That’s misinfo from anti-vaxxers, period. (src Eric Topol, see slides 4 + 5)

No, the approval wasn’t rushed. Because of the nature of a global pandemic, required thresholds for participation and data were reached MUCH faster than in cases of other illnesses thanks to > 4.3 BILLION doses (and counting) having been successfully administered! So researchers got all of that data and it’s confirmed to be safe and effective! (src: @jessicamalatyrivera, see slide 6)

We take/use all sorts of things that aren’t FDA approved every day (ahem multivitamins, alcohol, essential oils, shampoo) without thinking much about it. FDA approvals are not easy to get, and require rigorous analysis and proof. Feel rest assured by this. Science, and the sheer miracle of modern medicine and modern research, has brought us here. Doctors and healthcare workers brought us here. Medicine saves lives. Vaccines save lives. We are so gd lucky to be able to benefit from them.

Thank you to each and every person who’s worked on the frontline of this pandemic, who has saved lives, who has done this research and who has dedicated their lives to saving the lives of others. You are true heroes and icons. I don’t know how we can ever thank you enough. But I hope my eventual children get to see your faces and read your names in history books and know that you were the ones that made their lives possible. 🙏🏼
